    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_75_1825_11_01_page01.jpg"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>  
                        <note>16</note>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
                        <date when="1825-11-01">Nov.<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 1<hi rend="superscript">st.</hi> 1825</date>
                        <note>4</note>
                       
                    </dateline></opener>
            <p>
                    My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DumoE1">friend</persName> - Though<lb/>
                    - <hi rend="underline">you</hi> do not deserve that I<lb/>
                    should write to you, <hi rend="underline">your</hi><lb/>
                    ward <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ChauD1" cert="high">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> . Chauvet</persName> does -<lb/>
                    And I cannot on his <choice><orig>ac-<lb/>
                    =count</orig><reg>account</reg></choice> refrain from telling<lb/>
                    you how much we all<lb/>
                    like him- <del>and</del> Thank you<lb/>
                    for introducing him to us -<lb/>
                    - He is full of information<lb/>
                    yet desirous to obtain more<lb/>
                    - <del>and</del> the enlargement<lb/>
                    of his understanding <choice><orig>libera<lb/>
                    lity</orig><reg>liberality</reg></choice> of his views and<lb/>
                    warmth of his affections<lb/>
                    are all worthy of you<lb/></p>
                <p>
                    He will tell you better<lb/>
                    than I can <hi rend="underline">how we all do</hi> -<lb/>
                    -Strangers are often much<lb/>
                    better judges of these things<lb/>
                
                <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_75_1825_11_01_page02.jpg"/>
                    than those who see each other<lb/>
                    every day &amp; are prejudiced<lb/>
                    by their fears &amp; hopes -<lb/></p>
                <p>
                    I was much alarmed by<lb/>
                    the first sight of the pale<lb/>
                    thin figures &amp; faces of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">Fanny</persName><lb/>
                    and <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeS1">Sophy</persName> when they returned<lb/>
                    from their travels - But<lb/>
                    they are now in better<lb/>
                    plight and have some flesh<lb/>
                    on their poor little bones<lb/>
                    though as yet but little &amp;<lb/>
                    transient color in their<lb/>
                    cheeks - They frequently<lb/>
                    speak of you with affection<lb/>
                    &amp; gratitude - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">Fanny</persName> says<lb/>
                    you were her support and<lb/>
                    solace at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Geneva_SZ">Geneva</placeName> &amp; that<lb/>
                    without your kindness<lb/>
                    &amp; delightful conversation<lb/>
                    she could never have borne<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeS1">Sophy's</persName> illness and all her<lb/>
                    fears &amp; all her<lb/>
                
                <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_75_1825_11_01_page03.jpg"/>
                    <note>17</note>
                    own weakness. - She has<lb/>
                    given me a pretty little<lb/>
                    drawing of your <choice><orig>country<lb/>
                    =house</orig><reg>country house</reg></choice> &amp; has described it<lb/>
                    so well that we are all<lb/>
                    sure we have been aux<lb/>
                    philosophes &amp; have seen<lb/>
                    you there - We wish we<lb/>
                    could see you here - and<lb/>
                    are almost credulous<lb/>
                    enough to believe that<lb/>
                    you will really come<lb/>
                    next year-<lb/></p>
                <p>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> . Edgeworth</persName> &amp; my brothers<lb/>
                    and all my innumerable<lb/>
                    sisters - <hi rend="underline">4</hi> of whom you <choice><orig>al-<lb/>
                    ready</orig><reg>already</reg></choice> know &amp; love - viz<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauH1">Honora,</persName> <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">Fanny,</persName> <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeS1">Sophy</persName> - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeH1">Harriet</persName><lb/>
                    join in earnest entreaties<lb/>
                    that you will not disappoint<lb/>
                    them - and <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeL1">Lucy</persName> whom<lb/>
                    you will love too when you<lb/>
                    know <add>her</add> adds her sweet feeble<lb/>
                
                
                <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_75_1825_11_01_page04.jpg"/>
                    voice - She is <hi rend="underline">now</hi> recovering<lb/>
                    fast - can stand -&amp; walk<lb/>
                    a few steps - and will be<lb/>
                    able to walk to meet <add><persName ref="./Personography.xml#DumoE1">M. Dumont</persName></add> - next<lb/>
                    year -<lb/></p>
                <p>
                    When you have writt<unclear>en</unclear><lb/>
                    to me &amp; deserve to hear more,<lb/>
                    perhaps I may tell you <choice><orig>some<lb/>
                    -thing</orig><reg>something</reg></choice> more that may interest<lb/>
                    you concerning your friends<lb/>
                    here - But no more at <choice><orig>pre-<lb/>
                    sent</orig><reg>present</reg></choice> from<lb/></p>
                <closer>
                    y<hi rend="superscript">s</hi> . affectionately<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName><lb/></closer>
                <postscript><p>
                   <title ref="./Workography.xml#Harry1">Harry &amp; Lucy</title> will soon reach<lb/>
                    you if is has not already<lb/>
                    got to you -<lb/></p>
                <p>
                    I have just read &amp; very much<lb/>
                    like most part of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#StaeA2">M. de<lb/>
                    Staels</persName> <title ref="./Workography.xml#Lette6">Lettres sur l'Angleterre</title><lb/>
                    - I have written a long<lb/>
                    criticism to him -<lb/></p></postscript>
                
                
            </div>
        </body>
